title: For Sale:  M1 Garand - Springfield
postcontent:
It should be obvious that most of the Garand ads on Armslist are bogus scams offering a $1,000 or $2,000 Garand for $700 with a generic location like "North Carolina" instead of the town. The sellers won't meet in person and usually want the rifle shipped to some other address (My favorite is "I'm buying this for my dad. I'll pay for it, but can you ship it to him?). This is NOT one of those ads. My strong preference is for a face to face, cash sale. Because of the number of scamers that have responded to this ad I will only ship this rifle if it is paid for with a USPS money order. And I will only ship it to a valid FFL (01 or 03 C&R)... not some other address.
Not thrilled to sell this. However, I run gear-report.com and just bought a surplus Humvee as a field vehicle for the website... but I had not budgeted for it. So, I have to liquidate a few assets to cover the cost. If you go to my site and use the search bar at the top right to search for "Garand" you will find an articles and video about this VFW Garand and the other Garand I have for sale.
Springfield M1 GarandCame from CMP in a stock with a VFW sticker on it. 1.3M serial rangemuzzle 1+, Throat 4Barrel stamped "1 8 A 3 44"
Not interested in trades or low-ball offers.Strongly prefer a face to face sale in Burlington, NC. I am willing to ship to your FFL or C&R at your expense ONLY if payment is made with a USPS money order.  I had a rather convincing prospective buyer try to sucker me on a remote deal with payment by some othe means. Not dealing with that crap again.
